      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It's unlikely that a Wi-Fi signal \"follows\" someone physically; Wi-Fi signals work on radio waves which travel in all directions, not just in one direction. However, strong overlapping signals from neighboring Wi-Fi can create interference or connectivity issues for your device. It might also indicate your neighbor's Wi-Fi router is very close or crossed over path. To minimize interference, use a Wi-Fi analyzer app to find a clearer channel or reposition your router.",
