      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It's theoretically possible, though not by the name per se, for devices to use signal strength to infer movement; however, such monitoring would likely require more advanced technology than simply a name-setting on your neighbor's Wi-Fi router or the interaction of standard routers and wireless networks. Modern devices such as Wi-Fi routers typically do not possess the ability to track individual users as most Wi-Fi security protocols (like WPA3) are designed to keep traffic cryptographically separated. The strongest signal at your location may simply mean that your neighbor's router is close or has more power. If you're concerned about privacy, ensure that your Wi-Fi network is secured with a strong password (WPA3 if available), and that Smart Home devices have privacy settings configured correctly. If you suspect tampering, you could ask your neighbor for reassurance or involve your ISP or local authorities.",
